'From Squeak 2.4c of May 10, 1999 on 21 July 1999 at 3:20:22 pm'!"Change Set:		shiftClickFix-swDate:			21 July 1999Author:			Scott WallaceMakes it such that a shift-click in a list pane does NOT give keyboard focus to the item clicked on.  Among other things, this allows shift-click on a message name to result in the display of decompiled code in a Browser in Morphic, as it always has done in mvc Browsers."!!PluggableListMorph methodsFor: 'events' stamp: 'sw 7/21/1999 12:19'!wantsKeyboardFocusFor: aMorph	^ false! !!StringMorph methodsFor: 'editing' stamp: 'sw 7/21/1999 14:59'!handlesMouseDown: evt	^ (evt shiftPressed and: [self wantsKeyboardFocusOnShiftClick])		ifTrue: [self uncoveredAt: evt cursorPoint]		ifFalse: [super handlesMouseDown: evt].! !!StringMorph methodsFor: 'editing' stamp: 'sw 7/21/1999 14:59'!mouseDown: evt	"If the shift key is pressed, make this string the keyboard input focus."	(evt shiftPressed and: [self wantsKeyboardFocusOnShiftClick])		ifTrue: [evt hand newKeyboardFocus: self]		ifFalse: [super mouseDown: evt].! !!StringMorph methodsFor: 'editing' stamp: 'sw 7/21/1999 14:59'!wantsKeyboardFocusOnShiftClick	^ owner topRendererOrSelf wantsKeyboardFocusFor: self! !